ABBREVIATIONS

ICE4 = MPLAB® ICE 4 in-circuit emulator/production programmer
ICD5 = MPLAB ICD 5 in-circuit debugger/production programmer
ICD4 = MPLAB ICD 4 in-circuit debugger/production programmer
PK5 = MPLAB PICkit™ 5 in-circuit debugger/production programmer
PK4 = MPLAB PICkit 4 in-circuit debugger/production programmer
Snap = MPLAB Snap in-circuit debugger/development programmer

SW BP: Software Breakpoint
MCLR: Device pin used for Master Clear
LVP: Low voltage programming feature

BCM: Boot Configuration Memory used
Vpp: Device pin used for device programming
Pgm Pins: Device pins used for ICSP® programming/debug
Emu Pins: Device pins used for emulation/debug
